   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LETTERS FROM P'U T'IEN, FUKIEN PROVINCE One</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Greetings to the holy brothers, partakers together of the heavenly calling in the Lord, with the brothers who bear the responsibility as elders and deacons.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>May grace and peace be added to you from our Father, amen.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>I received good hospitality some time ago in Shanghai and was given many gifts which were really a sweet savor, an acceptable sacrifice, well-pleasing to God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>My God will fill your every need according to His riches, in glory, in Christ Jesus Phil 4:18-19 .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>It has been four weeks since I returned to P'u T'ien.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>I have been able to combine my work with my private affairs.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>I met with Brothers Ke San and Tsai Sheng in P'u T'ien, Han Chiang, and Yu Hsi.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>We will meet together for about four weeks.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>It is a good opportunity; thank the Lord for His grace.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>I apologize for not writing a letter of greeting sooner!</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Please forgive me in the Lord!</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Parts omitted.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Please let me know about the condition of the work in Shanghai and Brother Nee's health.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>May you be blessed with peace, joy and victory!</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Your brother,</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Faithful Luk</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Two</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Greetings to my beloved brother, Witness:</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>May the Lord's grace be with you, amen!</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>I received your letter and read it all.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>I heard that Brother Teng Ming was seriously sick; how is he now?</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>I am very worried about him.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>May the Lord heal him!</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Brother Nee is away, so your burden must be greater and heavier, but the grace of the Lord is sufficient for you.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>May the Lord use you much to edify many believers.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>I am ashamed that I am so useless.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Please pray for me much.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Last night I hurriedly translated several short stories.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>I enclose them to meet my responsibility.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Please do your best to edit them.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>There are places that are not fluent.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>I know that I cannot avoid them.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>I would not mind if you laughed at them, because you are beloved to me in the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Please forgive me!</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>When can you come to P'u T'ien to lead a meeting?</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>There are seven or eight brothers from Amoy who have all signed their names to a letter asking me to come with my family to work in Amoy.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>My future is unclear, and I do not know where to go.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>I am sure that the Lord who created me will lead me step by step.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>I am not sure about my trip to Hong Kong.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>I can only place this matter in the Lord's hands.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>I believe that when it is the appropriate time for the Lord, He will lead us.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>Has Miss Lee returned to Shanghai?</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Did Brother Chiang go ahead to Amoy to work?</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>May you have peace!</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>Your brother,</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>Faithful</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>A LETTER FROM AMOY, FUKIEN PROVINCE</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>To our dear brother in the Lord, Witness:</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>How is Brother Teng Ming's illness?</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>I hope you can keep me informed so that I will not worry.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>When will the second issue of The Christian be published?</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>How much will it cost to order one thousand copies?</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>When can it be sent to me?</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>I hope you will answer me so that I can wire the appropriate amount to you.</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>Brother Faithful Luk can come to Amoy to work tomorrow.</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>Please pray for this time of work!</S>
   <S PAR='58' RSNT='1' SNO='58'>I will tell you the rest later.</S>
   <S PAR='59' RSNT='1' SNO='59'>May you have peace!</S>
   <S PAR='60' RSNT='1' SNO='60'>Your brother,</S>
   <S PAR='61' RSNT='1' SNO='61'>James Chen</S>
   <S PAR='62' RSNT='1' SNO='62'>February 8, 1935</S>
   </TEXT>
